<dt id="section-2.6-1.9">When/by whom the keyword is set/cleared:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.6-1.10"> This keyword is set by an IMAP or JMAP server on messages it determines have an attachment. This can help mailbox clients indicate this to the user without having to fetch the full message body structure. Over JMAP, the "hasAttachment" Email property should indicate the same value.<a href="#section-2.6-1.10" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
