</dd>
          <dd class="break"></dd>
<dt id="section-2.7-1.9">When/by whom the keyword is set/cleared:</dt>
          <dd id="section-2.7-1.10"> This keyword is set by an IMAP or JMAP server on the user's copy of their vacation response and other automated messages sent on behalf of the user. Clients may use this to indicate to the user that this message was sent automatically, as if they have forgotten the rule or vacation response is set up they may be surprised to see it among their sent items.<a href="#section-2.7-1.10" class="pilcrow">¶</a>
</dd>
